</p><p class="- topic/p ">The line count pulses are triggered either by the encoder strip (during printing of a line) or by the carriage board itself (when active on the maintenance location). When data is left over after all the pulses given, or no data is available when giving pulses this error is reported.
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "/><tsCauses id="GUID-43CC1E6D-6B82-4D1B-AC52-4DB007D291E8" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "> Encoder strip misreading on PH carriage encoder strip.
